<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5482] Reduce number of jar invocations in the buildjars target</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5482</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When building derby.jar, derbytools.jar and derbynet.jar, the build script runs the jar target twice for each of the jars. The first jar invocation creates the jar and adds some files, and the second one updates the jars with some more files. It would be simpler to create each of the jar files in a single invocation, and it would also cut off a few seconds on the time to build the jars.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
